Description:
#shorts 
For 70% Discount on 3D Animation Course, Click here 👉🏻 professorofhow.com

Believe ME! Dandruff can cause a serious Scalp Infection 😱

Have you ever thought about why we get dandruff? Let's understand the science behind this.
This Malassezia Globosa fungus is responsible for dandruff present in your hairs.
This fungus makes the condition of your scalp very severe. So let's see what the hell is it doing in your hair.
This Malassezia globosa fungus is present on the skin of every person. And this fungus keeps consuming sebum, an oily substance present on your skin. But some people carry this fungus on their bodies in a very large amount.
The sebaceous gland present in the skin of these people keeps on producing that sebum to keep the skin and hair moist. And this Malassezia globosa keeps eating this sebum. The sebum is then metabolized by this fungus and a type of oleic acid is produced by this process. And this is the same acid that creates a dandruff-like condition on your scalp.
You must be aware that our skin cells get shredded off normally within 2-4 weeks, and their place is taken by the new cells.
But in some people, the dead cells start to make dandruff-like flakes within only 7 days, and the reason behind this is oleic acid.
And this dandruff causes very severe itching on your scalp. But in some cases, this condition gets even worse, which is called Seborrheic Dermatitis.

Title: Team Medium Rare or Well Done? #shorts
Description:
Are you team Medium Rare or Well Done? 🥩

A raging debate more controversial than ones political beliefs, that I’m sure will continue in the comment section. Here is my perspective:

People should enjoy what they like and should not be judged for it. However, I do believe that objectively, certain cuts are optimized at different temperatures based on 3 variables: tenderness, juiciness, and flavor. Here are some examples:

Filet mignon: extremely lean and tender meaning it will quickly deteriorate and dry out if over cooked. For that reason a low temperature between 120-130F (rare) is often preferred. Cook a filet to 165F (well done) and the result will be extremely dry. 

Brisket: filled with collagen and extremely tough, only becoming tender and juicy at high temps. Taking it up to a high internal temp between 200-210F (well done) is preferred. Cook a brisket to medium rare, and the result will be inedibly chewy.

As such, internal temps are highly dependent on the cut of beef itself!

Another critical piece of information is that some cultures commonly consume cuts that are optimized at lower temps while others primarily eat cuts that are high in collagen and require “well done”. I think this contributes to such strong and often conflicting opinions of the best way to cook beef.

With that said, I highly encourage you to continue experimenting and finding your own preference.

Title: 'Shocking' science behind SNEEZING! - By Kishor Singh #shorts
Description:
For 70% Discount on 3D Animation Course, Click here 👉🏻 professorofhow.com

'Shocking' science behind SNEEZING! - By Kishor Singh #shorts 

You are right if you think that sneezing is a natural process to clear all the foreign particles present in your nose. However, the real question is how our nose gets to know that it has to get rid of these foreign particles?
Whenever any dirt or dust particle enters your nose, these particles produce irritation in these tiny cilia. After that, these cilia send a signal to your brain through the trigeminal nerve and indicate our brain to clear all the foreign particles present in our nose at a particular time. 
In response to this signal, our brain instructs our body to sneeze and get rid of these tiny particles. Following the order of your brain, your respiratory system tells your lungs to store a high amount of air in them. Before releasing this air out, your tongue gets its position at the top of your mouth. Alongside this, your eyes shut off and facial muscles get stretched.
The air that was stored in your lungs, gets out of your mouth and nose in the form of a sneeze. All this process gifts a relaxation mode to the cilia by releasing those foreign particles, mucus, and tiny water droplets out of your mouth at the speed of 160kmph.

Title: Does Clear Ice Really Make a Difference? #shorts
Description:
Does Clear Ice Make a Difference in Your Drink? 
In the previous episode where I made a Clear Ice Diamond, I mentioned that Japanese bartenders use clear ice since it chills drink better and dilutes slower. So I needed to test it myself.
In my warm room, I prepared one clear and one cloudy cube with a weight of 102 grams.
Added  2 oz | 60 ml of Jim Beam Bourbon and stir them both 20 times. Let it sit there for 10 minutes. The cloudy ice temperature was 39.9°F | 4.4°C And in the Clear ice 36.7°F | 2.6°C weight difference was 7 grams.
I used a pour tester, and it showed that the difference was 1/4 oz | 7.4 ml

บางคนขึ้นเป็นนายกรัฐมนตรีเพื่อสร้างชาติ แต่บางคนกลับใช้ตำแหน่งนั้นเพื่อ กดขี่ประชาชน และโกงกินประเทศตัวเอง! คลิปนี้จะพาคุณไปเปิดโปง ผู้นำโลก ที่ไม่ได้เป็นเพียงแค่ผู้นำที่ล้มเหลว แต่คือ "นายกรัฐมนตรีที่เลวที่สุดในโลก" อย่างแท้จริง!
เรารวบรวม 5 ผู้นำที่โลกไม่มีวันลืม ทั้งในเรื่อง คอร์รัปชัน, การ ใช้อำนาจเผด็จการ, และการ เอาเปรียบประชาชน อย่างไม่รู้จักพอ 
เช่น อิดี อามิน (ยูกันดา) – เผด็จการโหดเหี้ยม ผู้สังหารประชาชนกว่า 300,000 คน
เบนจามิน เนทันยาฮู (อิสราเอล) – นายกฯ ที่พัวพันคดีคอร์รัปชัน แต่ยังเกาะเก้าอี้แน่น
ฮุน เซน (กัมพูชา) – ผู้นำที่อยู่ในอำนาจกว่า 38 ปี ใช้กฎหมายและทหารปราบฝ่ายตรงข้าม และกดขี่ประชาชน
โรเบิร์ต มูกาเบ (ซิมบับเว) – ผู้นำที่ทำเศรษฐกิจพัง เงินเฟ้อพุ่งจนต้องหิ้วเงินเป็นกระสอบไปซื้อขนมปัง
ไปจนถึง นิโคลา มาดูโร (เวเนซุเอลา) – ผู้นำที่เปลี่ยนประเทศร่ำรวยน้ำมันให้กลายเป็นรัฐล้มเหลว
📌 ถ้าคุณสนใจเรื่อง การเมืองโลก, ผู้นำที่อันตราย, หรืออยากรู้ว่าใครคือคนที่ทำลายประเทศตัวเองได้มากที่สุด… คลิปนี้ห้ามพลาดเด็ดขาด!

Title: Red Velvet Cookies! Recipe tutorial #Shorts
Description:
How to make soft and chewy Red Velvet Cookies!

Hey guys, I'm Eloise! I make simple recipe tutorials across my social media

My main YouTube Channel is: @Fitwaffle 

You guys know how cookie obsessed I am! I’m also totally obsessed with everything red velvet ❤️ so these cookies are just an absolute dream 🤤

They’re super quick and easy to make. They have a subtle chocolate and vanilla taste and they’re packed with milk and white chocolate chips 🙌

Sound on for full instructions 🔉

All you need is:
115g unsalted butter, melted
150g light brown sugar
115g granulated sugar
1 large egg
2 tsp vanilla extract
Strong red food colouring (I used Sugarflair Red Extra)
170g plain flour
10g cocoa powder
1/2 tsp bicarbonate of soda
1/2 tsp salt
100g white chocolate chips
75g milk or dark chocolate chips

Makes about 20-23 cookies

Bake 160C (fan) 8-10 minutes - allow to cool for 10 minutes before transferring to a cooling rack

Happy Baking everybody!

The texture is just like Subway cookies!

Title: Easy Reflection in PROCREATE #Shorts - Quick Procreate Tutorial
Description:
Procreate Short Tutorial!
In this short video I will show you how you can easily create a reflection in Procreate.

Want more short tutorials? Leave a comment!

In this short Procreate tutorial we'll do the following to create a reflection
✔ Duplicate the layer with the photo
✔ Set the layer blending mode to Darker Color (or to Lighter Color if your photo has a black background)
✔ Go to the Move and Transform tool and turn on magnetics
✔ Flip the layer vertical and drag it down
✔ Lower the opacity of the reflection layer to about 50%
✔ Add a mask to the reflection layer
✔ Use a soft brush set to black to mask the lower half of the reflection

Now you'll never wonder how to create a reflectionin Procreate again!
